Time for recreation is rare as an academic, but the time that one doesn't spend at the desk, the best thoughts come.
Striving more to publish more does not always lead to better results. One must not forget to recover if one wants to become a better scientist.
So I'm recharging my batteries again:
Use both halves of the brain. 🧠
As scientists, we often use the analytical parts of our brain. But if I use the creative part (e.g. by playing guitar, painting, etc.) as well as the analytical part of my brain, it's as if my mental capacities have increased. Through this, I become better in both areas.
Train the muscles, not just the head. 💪
Sport is not just something for future triathletes or people who want to look better. Sport also improves the quality of life. Thoughts, mood, productivity - everything is connected. Taking a break and stepping away from the computer makes the time away from the computer more productive again.
Permission to relax. 📺
Recharging the batteries doesn't just mean buying new ones. A good film or a good book can have the same effect as creative work and physical activity. It is important to be aware that it is okay to relax and do nothing. There is no room for feelings of guilt here!
Among those things, I noticed that they help me to recover. But there are still many others. What do we do to continue to be fascinated by science and not get burned out? 🤔
#academic #science #promotion #phdlife #typefully
